SIMPLE: oppressive
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oppressive
<hw>Op*press"ive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>oppressif</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Unreasonably burdensome;
unjustly severe, rigorous, or harsh; <as>as, <ex>oppressive</ex> taxes;
<ex>oppressive</ex> exactions of service; an <ex>oppressive</ex> game
law.</as></def> <rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Using oppression; tyrannical; <as>as,
<ex>oppressive</ex> authority or commands</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Heavy; overpowering; hard to be borne; creating a
sense of heavy burden; <as>as, <ex>oppressive</ex> grief or woe;
<ex>oppressive</ex> heat or humidity; an <ex>oppressive</ex>
workload</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>To ease the soul of one <qex>oppressive</qex> weight.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Op*press"ive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Op*press"ive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oppressor</ent>⟦br⟧
